● Found the issue. The model load is gated on `wasLoadedBefore()`
  (sessionStorage), but **`buildPanel()` always shows the intro/load-button
  regardless** — only `autoRestorePanel()` (which fires only when the panel
  was *open* on the previous page) honors the flag. So if you close the
  panel before clicking next, the new page treats you like a first-time
  visitor.

The fix: extract the auto-load logic into a helper and call it from
  `buildPanel()` whenever `wasLoadedBefore()` is true. Then opening the
  panel via the FAB on a new page auto-loads from cache instead of showing
  the button again.

