● Syntax check passed. The fix is in place.

**What it does:**
- Before: opening the panel on a new page always called `buildIntroPanel()`
  → "Load model" button visible → user had to click again, even though the
  3.1 GB Gemma weights are still cached in IndexedDB from the prior page.
- After: `buildPanel()` checks `wasLoadedBefore()` (sessionStorage flag set
  after the first successful load this tab). If true, it skips the intro
  entirely and runs the same auto-load path that previously only fired when
  the panel was already open during navigation. The cached weights stream in
  near-instantly via the brief progress UI; composer enables on its own;
  conversation history restores.

**How it works (technical):**
- Extracted the auto-load body from `autoRestorePanel()` into a new helper
  `restoreLoadedSession(panel, body)`.
- `buildPanel()` now branches on `wasLoadedBefore()`: if true, calls
  `restoreLoadedSession`; else calls `buildIntroPanel` (first-ever-visit
  behavior is unchanged).
- `autoRestorePanel()` is now a small shim that just opens the panel — the
  auto-load happens inside `buildPanel`, so both code paths (panel-open
  during nav, panel-closed-then-FAB-clicked on new page) get the same
  behavior.

**One caveat worth knowing:** `wasLoadedBefore()` reads from
  `sessionStorage`, which clears when the tab closes. If you close the tab
  and reopen the site fresh later, you'll still see the load button on the
  first page (even though the cache is intact), but every subsequent page in
  that new tab will auto-load. If you want truly cross-tab persistence, the
  simplest one-line change is to switch `STATE_KEYS.loaded` to
  `localStorage`. Happy to make that change too if you want — just say the
  word.

