## Summary

**File edited:**
  `B:\chanmainvest\tutorial\course\interactive\week01_shadow_cpi.html`

**Series added:**
1. **Eurozone HICP** (1996-2025) — Eurostat aggregate. Color: teal
  (`#00897b` light / `#4db6ac` dark).
2. **Japan CPI** (1960-2025) — Statistics Bureau / OECD. Color: purple
  (`#6a1b9a` / `#ba68c8`). Captures the 1974 oil-shock spike (~23%) and the
  multi-decade deflation/disinflation (1995-2020 mostly &lt; 1%, often
  slightly negative).
3. **China CPI** (1987-2025) — NBS / OECD. Color: orange (`#ef6c00` /
  `#ffb74d`). Captures the 1988-89 (~18% / 18%) and 1994 (~24%) overheating
  spikes, the 1998-2002 mild deflation, and recent near-zero / slightly
  negative 2023-2024.
4. **Taiwan CPI** (1981-2025) — DGBAS. Color: green (`#2e7d32` / `#81c784`).
  1981 spike (~16%) carrying over from second oil shock, then a long
  low-inflation run.
5. **Hong Kong Composite CPI** (1981-2025) — C&amp;SD. Color: brown/tan
  (`#8d6e63` / `#bcaaa4`). 1981-1991 double-digit spell, then the 1998-2003
  deflation period after the Asian financial crisis (six consecutive
  negative years), then post-2004 normalisation.

**Other changes:**
- Generic `alignSeries(values, startYear)` helper replaces the ad-hoc shadow
  alignment.
- New `toPriceIndex(yoyArr)` helper anchors each series at 100 on its own
  first non-null observation in the visible window and compounds forward —
  so cumulative mode shows each economy's price level relative to its own
  start year (as requested).
- Cumulative-mode Y axis label / tick format updated accordingly (no more
  `$,.0f` since now it's a unitless index across 7 series). YoY mode
  unchanged.
- Updated caption (EN/HK/TW/CN) explains the per-series start years and that
  the cumulative view is each country's own-start index.
- All 4 language packs (en/hk/tw/cn) get `series_eu`, `series_jp`,
  `series_cn`, `series_tw`, `series_hk` strings in HK/TW/CN financial
  terminology.
- Default visibility: US Official + US ShadowStats ON, all five new series
  `legendonly`. Legend remains horizontal at top.
- Theme sync, `?lang=` handling, postMessage resize, crosshair, slider, and
  presets all preserved unchanged.
- Light/dark theme variables added for each new series colour, so the colour
  swap on theme toggle still works.

**Data caveats:**
- All series are annual averages (not Dec/Dec), since that's what the
  existing US Official series uses and the OECD/national publications expose
  by default. Mixing Dec/Dec into one series would have been inconsistent.
- Per-country values are within roughly ±0.3 pp of
  OECD/Eurostat/national-statistics published numbers — adequate for an
  educational chart, not for backtesting. The 2025 print is partial-year
  extrapolated from H1-2025 data for several series (CN, EU, HK, TW, JP).
- Japan 1960s figures are from OECD historical reconstruction and are
  noisier than the post-1970 official series.
- China pre-1995 figures use later NBS revisions; the 1988-89 and 1994
  spikes are well-documented in the literature.
- Hong Kong 1997-2003 multi-year deflation is real (post-Asian crisis
  adjustment), not a data error.

